pipeline_summary.name: multi_region_ecommerce_analytics
pipeline_summary.description: Multi-region ecommerce analytics pipeline that ingests sales data from four regions, converts currencies to USD, and aggregates a global revenue report.

components.name: Start Pipeline
components.description: Marks the entry point of the pipeline and triggers the parallel ingestion stage.

upstream_policy.description: No upstream dependencies; this is the pipeline entry.

components.name: Ingest Sales Data
components.description: Extracts regional sales CSV files for USEast, USWest, EU and APAC into XCom objects for downstream processing.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after the start_pipeline marker completes successfully.

components.name: Convert Currency to USD
components.description: Normalises regional sales amounts to USD; noop for US regions and applies static exchange rates for EU (EURUSD) and APAC (JPYUSD).

upstream_policy.description: Executes after the corresponding ingest_sales_data task finishes.

components.name: Aggregate Global Revenue
components.description: Combines the USDconverted regional sales data into a single global revenue report CSV.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after all four convert_currency tasks have completed successfully.

connections.purpose: Write the aggregated global revenue CSV

components.name: End Pipeline
components.description: Marks successful completion of the pipeline after the global aggregation step.

upstream_policy.description: Executes after aggregate_global_revenue finishes without errors.

connections.purpose: Read the final global revenue CSV

description.default: Multi-region ecommerce analytics pipeline that ingests sales data from four regions, converts currencies to USD, and aggregates a global revenue report.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

region.description: Geographic region to ingest sales data from
Geographic region whose currency will be converted to USD

provide_context.description: Flag to enable XCom context access for aggregation

sources: Regional sales CSV files for USEast, USWest, EU, and APAC stored in the filesystem at /data/sales
sinks: Global revenue report CSV written back to the filesystem at /data/sales (e.g., global_revenue_report_20240101.csv)
intermediate_datasets: XCom objects containing raw sales data per region (sales_data_US-East, sales_data_US-West, sales_data_EU, sales_data_APAC)
XCom objects containing USDconverted data per region (converted_data_US-East, converted_data_US-West, converted_data_EU, converted_data_APAC)
Inmemory aggregated dataset before final CSV serialization
